acceptance_criteria: "Repository-local .agents/pm is initialized and committed with durable .toon items and .jsonl history.; All actionable security, dependency, code, CI, and documentation findings are fixed or explicitly documented with rationale.; The final pushed head passes the complete release verification surface."
value: Protect users and maintainers while keeping the agent-oriented Jellyfin CLI dependable and releasable.
impact: "Eliminates known dependency exposure, fixes user-visible output defects, and creates durable project lineage."
outcome: "Zero actionable dependency alerts, green release validation, resolved product defects, and complete repository-local pm history."
why_now: GitHub reports critical/high dependency alerts and issue #23 documents broken session output behavior.
